RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 41. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PEACEFUL MOMENT vied for the early lead, was slightly pressured by an outside foe, stayed along the rail and attended the paced, shook challenger as she pleased at the three eighths pole and drew off. ROSALIE'S DESTINY stalked the early leaders from the three path while matching strides with an outside foe, advanced position at the three eighths pole where she shook her company and went on after the leader, ran a game race but was second best today. DANCING TRICK was off a bit slow and settled off the pace for the first half of the race, was asked as the half mile marker and briefly responded, was able to maintain position and finish third. SECRET MOMENT vied for the early lead, settled just off the leaders hip, from the three and four path, stayed on until the three eighths pole and retreated. JIVIN ASTRO stalked the early leaders from the four path, matched strides with an inside foe early on, tired after the three eighths pole. MY RAINBOW was never involved.

ENTRY.NAME: Rosalie's Destiny
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, 3w, matched strides, advanced 1/4, up for second

ENTRY.NAME: Jivin Astro
ENTRY.OWNER: Jarrett Jr Terrell and Lara Racing Stables LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, matched strides with inside foe while off the pace, tire

ENTRY.NAME: Peaceful Moment
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, led, rail trip, pressured briefly, drew off, much the best

ENTRY.NAME: Dancing Trick
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, settled in hands, cued at the 1/2, maintained position

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 13750. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 13, 2022. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 13, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THERIDEOFALIFETIME was the fastest out of the gates and took the lead early on, she traveled in the two path around the track as she set the fractions as she pleased, was given the cue at the quarter pole where she drew off and won by many. POST CLOSE settled off the pace in the seven path, angled in a bit into the four path while stalking the early leaders, edged out at the the half mile pole to the five path where he passed horses on the outside while gaining position, stayed four wide into the turn, angled down to the rail leaving the turn taking advantage of a hole that opened up and closed along the rail getting up for second. WEDINGTON vied for the lead early, smartly settled off the pace from the three and four path, settled in that position and maintained that position through out. BODEE BODEE was off a step slow and trailed early on, was given time to find his stride, was asked to start gaining ground at the half mile pole, he started to gain ground and build momentum, was encouraged and kept gaining ground while circling the field through the turn, angled in five wide in the stretch where he passed tired foes and out finished the rest. TROPHY DADDY made no impact. SUN SQUALL stalked and then faded. REDIVIVUS showed brief speed and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Redivivus
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed brief speed and then faded

ENTRY.NAME: Post Close
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled off the pace, 7w, angled in 4w, advanced 1/2, closed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 13 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs. (If deemed inadvisabl e by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE NEXT BIG BLING was allowed to find her stride out of the gates, settled off the pace in a stalking position, stalked from the three path until the stretch, was driven and encouraged to keep closing in on the early leader from the three path past the sixteenth pole, where she was able to run down and over come the early leader, and get up for the win. GET OUT TONIGHT vied for the early lead, attended the pace from the rail until the sixteenth pole, was collared by an outside challenger, relinquished the lead and had to settle for second place honors today. KANCANCUTIE no menace. JAZLA saved ground while racing along the rail, raced even today and showed no late kick. QUEEN OF MAGNOLIA was never involved.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For A Claiming Price Of Less Than $25,000).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SCARLETTA stalked the early pace while racing in the three path, was pressured by an outside competitor until the half mile pole, shook that that challenger, advanced and gained ground through the turn, challenged the early leader at the seven sixteenth pole, over came that foe, was challenged by an inside foe who was racing along the rail, battled with that rival down the stretch, while having an outside rival threaten, was kept on point and driven and proved the best today after racing a game race. REAUX BINA rated off the pace along the rail early on, took a ground saving trip through out, was able to advance along the rail after the three eighths pole, continued to gain ground and passed up the fence at the quarter pole, was driven and encouraged, battled for the win but came up short today and had to settle for second. DREWSILLA went six wide through the first turn, stalked from the outside down the back stretch, gained ground while in the four path through the second turn, was asked for more in the stretch to no avail. RELAY vied for the early lead while taking a ground saving trip along the rail, was pressured after the half mile pole by a rival closing from the outside, was collared by the quarter pole and faltered after that. SMART IZZY four wide early and made no impact. GRACEFUL STREET trailed through out.

ENTRY.OWNER: Roe Steve D and Roe Patricia L

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SADIE'S RANSOM took the lead early, was able to attend the pace, was uncontested and drew off for a win by a large margin. B B GUN BULLSEYE raced from the inside while off the pace, asked and gained ground after the half mile pole, continued to close and make up ground into deep stretch, up for second. DONTFORGETRDREAMS was off a step slow, settled off the pace while racing mid pack, gained ground and moved into a stalking position, was in contention then faded late. AGGIE DOCTOR settled off the pace early, raced in mid pack, showed little after that. OUR CUSTOM DARLING showed brief speed early on while stalking the leader, then faded through out the lader part of the race. DORGENOIS was never involved. GATSBY'S GIFT made no impact.

SMARTY ALEX settled off the pace for the first half mile, was asked and responded by gaining ground and building momentum while closing in on the early leaders, passed one of the early leaders at the quarter pole, had aim on the other one but couldn't get there in time and had to settle for second. RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEATED ARGUMENT raced from off the pace early while encouraged to improve position, advanced in between horses to settle on the outside just off of the the early leaders, was pushed and encouraged to continue to close ground, was ridden out of the turn and five wide in the upper stretch, was driven to stay on point and raced determinedly to take the win.
